brainly_data.question: Mistletoe is a plants that absorbs nutrients from living oak trees. this causes damage to the tree. which of these relationships exists between the mistletoe and the oak tree?
brainly_data.subject: Biology

all_answers.question: Mistletoe is a plants that absorbs nutrients from living oak trees. this causes damage to the tree. which of these relationships exists between the mistletoe and the oak tree?
all_answers.subject: Biology
all_answers.text: The mistletoe is considered a parasite. Only one living thing benefits from the relationship between the two organisms
